President Trump commends Congress for its bipartisan effort in addressing the opioid crisis and acknowledges their commitment to mobilizing the largest legislative effort in history. He emphasizes that addressing this crisis has been a top priority since the beginning of his administration. The president directed his administration to allocate unprecedented resources to combat the devastating impact of the opioid crisis on communities throughout the country. The SUPPORT for Patients and Communities Act (H.R. 6) is praised for its investments that aim to help individuals overcome addiction, prevent illicit drugs from entering communities, raise public awareness, and save lives. President Trump expresses gratitude to the leaders of the House and Senate committees who contributed to this significant legislation and recognizes their exceptional leadership in strengthening public health and safety responses. The president looks forward to signing this historic legislation.